---
description: Match process depth to task complexity. No unconditional ceremony.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Trivial tasks (single file, low risk, clear intent) use /oodaloop-quick. No planning phase required.
- Medium tasks (multi-file, moderate risk) use Observe -> Orient -> Decide -> Act minimum.
- Complex tasks (architectural, high risk, multi-system) use full OODA with Loop reassessment.
- Never force heavyweight process on lightweight work. Never skip verification on risky work.
- If a task escalates in complexity mid-execution, pause and upgrade the process level.
- If process feels like overhead without safety benefit, reduce it.
- When a skill defines a precondition-failure path, follow it exactly. Do not reinterpret user intent, read adjacent skills, or improvise recovery to justify bypassing the gate. Report the failure, recommend the prescribed fix, and stop.
